The paper deals with face recognition systems based on deep neural networks, which is a topic closely related to computer vision (cs.CV). The study also involves the vulnerabilities of the system, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed neighborly de-convolutional neural network (NbNet) is a machine learning model, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves experiments and evaluations, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM).
